abstract: The couple met in 2014 through OkCupid in New York.
snippet: The couple met in 2014 through OkCupid in New York.
lead_paragraph: Lindsay Grace Vogelman and Benjamin Lewis Bell were married Dec. 14 at 501 Union, an events space in Brooklyn. Marcia J. Sikowitz, a judge for the Kings County Housing Court in Brooklyn and an aunt of the bride, officiated.

abstract: In a story Dec. 13, 2019, about the Supreme Court agreeing to hear President Donald Trump’s pleas to keep his tax, bank and financial records private, The Associated Press erroneously reported in some versions that Trump had stated during the 2016 campaign that he couldn’t be prosecuted or investigated as president even if he were to shoot someone on New York’s Fifth Avenue.
snippet: In a story Dec. 13, 2019, about the Supreme Court agreeing to hear President Donald Trump’s pleas to keep his tax, bank and financial records private, The Associated Press erroneously reported in some versions that Trump had stated during the 2016...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In a story Dec. 13, 2019, about the Supreme Court agreeing to hear President Donald Trump’s pleas to keep his tax, bank and financial records private, The Associated Press erroneously reported in some versions that Trump had stated during the 2016 campaign that he couldn’t be prosecuted or investigated as president even if he were to shoot someone on New York’s Fifth Avenue.

abstract: Mr. Hatcher was one of the first two black people elected in 1967 as mayor of a large American city.
snippet: Mr. Hatcher was one of the first two black people elected in 1967 as mayor of a large American city.
lead_paragraph: Richard G. Hatcher, one of the nation’s first big-city black mayors who in two decades leading Gary, Ind., sought vainly to stem its poverty and blight while championing cities and blacks generally, died on Friday night in Chicago. He was 86.

abstract: Nicaragua's National Assembly on Saturday approved nationalizing a major gas station company two days after the United States imposed sanctions on it for allegedly being used by President Daniel Ortega's family to finance and launder money for the government.
snippet: Nicaragua's National Assembly on Saturday approved nationalizing a major gas station company two days after the United States imposed sanctions on it for allegedly being used by President Daniel Ortega's family to finance and launder money for the...
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Nicaragua's National Assembly on Saturday approved nationalizing a major gas station company two days after the United States imposed sanctions on it for allegedly being used by President Daniel Ortega's family to finance and launder money for the government.
headline_main: Nicaragua Nationalizes Major Gas Station Chain Linked to Ortega
headline_print_headline: Nicaragua Nationalizes Major Gas Station Chain Linked to Ortega

abstract: NEW YORK — Felix Rohatyn, the financier and government adviser who was credited with helping to save New York City from ruin during the 1970s as chairman of the agency that oversaw the city's finances, died Saturday. He was 91.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Felix Rohatyn, the financier and government adviser who was credited with helping to save New York City from ruin during the 1970s as chairman of the agency that oversaw the city's finances, died Saturday. He was 91.
headline_main: Banker, New York City Savior Felix Rohatyn Dies at 91
headline_print_headline: Banker, New York City Savior Felix Rohatyn Dies at 91

abstract: A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
snippet: A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A Democratic U.S. lawmaker who opposed his party's moves to impeach President Donald Trump told staff on Saturday he will become a Republican as soon as next week, the New York Times reported, citing unnamed sources familiar with the discussions.
headline_main: Democrat Lawmaker Opposed to Impeachment Will Switch Parties: Report
headline_print_headline: Democrat Lawmaker Opposed to Impeachment Will Switch Parties: Report

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates pledged to boost funding for public schools, increase teacher salaries and reduce college debt at a Saturday forum that cast a rare spotlight on education, an issue that has received only passing attention in recent debates.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates pledged to boost funding for public schools, increase teacher salaries and reduce college debt at a Saturday forum that cast a rare spotlight on education, an issue that has received only passing attention in rec...
lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — Democratic presidential candidates pledged to boost funding for public schools, increase teacher salaries and reduce college debt at a Saturday forum that cast a rare spotlight on education, an issue that has received only passing attention in recent debates.
headline_main: Democratic Hopefuls Pledge More Money for Schools, Teachers
headline_print_headline: Democratic Hopefuls Pledge More Money for Schools, Teachers

abstract: Nine presidential candidates have signed a letter urging the D.N.C. to adjust its qualification criteria for January and February.
snippet: Nine presidential candidates have signed a letter urging the D.N.C. to adjust its qualification criteria for January and February.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — At the urging of Senator Cory Booker of New Jersey, eight Democratic presidential candidates, and Mr. Booker, have signed a letter urging Tom Perez, the Democratic National Committee chairman, to lower the thresholds to qualify for the party’s January and February debates.

abstract: Mexico's deputy foreign minister, Jesus Seade, said on Saturday he sent a letter to the top U.S. trade official expressing surprise and concern over a labor enforcement provision proposed by a U.S. congressional committee in the new North American trade deal.
snippet: Mexico's deputy foreign minister, Jesus Seade, said on Saturday he sent a letter to the top U.S. trade official expressing surprise and concern over a labor enforcement provision proposed by a U.S. congressional committee in the new North American...
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Mexico's deputy foreign minister, Jesus Seade, said on Saturday he sent a letter to the top U.S. trade official expressing surprise and concern over a labor enforcement provision proposed by a U.S. congressional committee in the new North American trade deal.
headline_main: Mexico Objects to Labor Enforcement Provision in North American Trade Deal
headline_print_headline: Mexico Objects to Labor Enforcement Provision in North American Trade Deal

abstract: The aide, John McEntee, had been dismissed in 2018 on the orders of the chief of staff at the time, John F. Kelly.
snippet: The aide, John McEntee, had been dismissed in 2018 on the orders of the chief of staff at the time, John F. Kelly.
lead_paragraph: A close aide to President Trump who was dismissed last year by the White House chief of staff at the time is expected to rejoin the West Wing, according to three people familiar with the move.
